From 4ac14cf1e7ca6c71cf35f8c4d927d875486c961d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 22:35:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mdev: add missing braces around else branch in device node
 creation

The else branch of the device node path construction was missing braces,
causing a spurious indentation and potential scope issues. Add braces to
match the surrounding code style.

Found during Phase 3 (core service stability) testing on the hybris_generic
LXC container target.

Change-Id: I8127c3df6ab0575883a4050ed53e069a1ead7ab3
---
 toys/pending/mdev.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/toys/pending/mdev.c b/toys/pending/mdev.c
index eb44d9d..fc3d789 100644
--- a/toys/pending/mdev.c
+++ b/toys/pending/mdev.c
@@ -231,8 +231,9 @@ found_device:
         else mkdir(toybuf, 0755);
       }
     }
-    else
+    else {
       sprintf(toybuf, "/dev/%s", device_name);
+    }
 
       if ((temp=getenv("ACTION")) && !strcmp(temp, "remove")) {
         unlink(toybuf);
-- 
2.50.1

